From Brian Keith Michalk Subject Re high speed rail is bad In article David McGaughey writes The question I think then becomes Do we the general public need the train I certainly do not nor will I ever need this train in Lubbock With the inexpensive air travel provided between Dallas and Houston I don't think people in Dallas or Houston need it I totally Really the only people this is going to benefit are those who live in the cities where the train Who wants to drive to the train station from X Lubbock for example It's probably farther to drive to the train station than it is to the nearest national I really can't see spending billion on a system that only three cities will benefit